            <biogHist>
                <p>William John Watson was born in Kilmuir-Easter parish, Ross-shire, in February
                    1865. His parents were Hugh Watson, blacksmith, and Maria Watson n√©e Ross. After
                    serving as rector at Inverness Royal Academy then at Edinburgh's Royal High
                    School, he was appointed Professor of Celtic at the University of Edinburgh,
                    occupying the chair from 1914 - 1938. In 1926, he published <span
                        localType="mods-titleinfo">The History of the Celtic Place Names of
                        Scotland</span>, his major work and an ambitious project.</p>
